canvas_summaries.ocr_text: EQUAL PAY- Why it will be in the National Interest IN proportion to its size and population our country has made a contribution to the waging of this war incomparably greater than that made by any other nation. In 1940 we stood alone to safeguard the world for freedom and democracy. We have an equally important contribution to make in the post- war world towards maintaining Peace and the freedom which has been so dearly bought. We must mobilise our best brains and characters now to deal with the problems ahead, and as a first step we must give the Rate for the Job. That will enable us to find the right people for the right positions, and we shall have real equality of opportunity. In this we are not ahead of other Nations — WE LAG BEHIND! EQUAL PAY Russia, America and part of China are far ahead of us in granting equal pay. These countries have proved it to be beneficial and in the national interest. How much longer are we going to allow them to leap ahead in post- war Recon struction? [ WORK Wo Britain Tags behind

If appointments are made on merit, irrespective of sex, the best brains and general ability receive recogni tion and work is done by those best able to do it. This means that the quality of our products will steadily improve and our export trade expand. Industry must benefit if people are doing the work for which they are best suited instead of that for which they have no special aptitude or liking simply because their labour is cheapest and most readily available. but bon SURE SACKED SHE' S CHEAPER.

canvas_summaries.ocr_text: EQUAL PAY FOR EQUAL WORK Why it will help to bring Peace to the World Because: NLY great wisdom and vision, allied to constructive imagination, can deal with the complex problems of the post- war world. These are the gifts of the few, and only given to some men and women. We need to make full use of all who are especially gifted. We just cannot afford to be limited to one sex when choosing our Leaders and Executives. Until we have Equal Pay for Equal Work the status of women workers will be lower than that of men and there will not be equality of opportunity for service. Om lan If we choose leaders mainly from the male sex there will be a terrible wastage of ability which is sorely needed to guide us to peace, prosperity and inter national understanding. Equal Pay for Equal Work is in the Best Interests of IS

canvas_summaries.ocr_text: THE RATE FOR THE JOB Why it will maintain Fair Wage Standards W HERE you have the Rate- for- the- job there will be no undercutting. In America, where Equal Pay in the Civil Service and the Teaching Profession is established, it has been proved to be of benefit. If you have women competing with men for the same job at lower pay, the women have little incentive to give of their best. They appreciate that they are neither engaged nor promoted on merit and may never compete on fair terms with men. Male labour also suffers if it is considered on no more convincing grounds than sex discrimination. On that basis, neither sex has proper opportunity for discover ing which work it can most ably perform. Square pegs in round holes always have and always will make the machinery squeak! America, Russia and China are not blind to these simple facts. WHAT MUST THEY THINK OF US? Are you for lagging or for leading? Because they will be engaged for their capacity and employed on work for which they are best suited. Because they will have a happy and contented staff.

canvas_summaries.ocr_text: EQUAL PAY FOR EQUAL WORK Why it is in the best interests of the Home The Rate- for- the- Job is in the best interests of the home for a very large number of reasons. Marriage, if it is rightly based and leads to the foundation of a true home and healthy, happy family life, is the supreme career for a woman. It should be regarded as a career and entered upon with full appreciation of its poten tialities, responsibilities and opportunities. O It should never be undertaken as the easiest means of obtaining leisure and security. Marriage entered upon in that spirit often ends in disillusioned parents, broken homes, and unhappy undisciplined children. Women should be able to earn security and apprecia tion of special ability as a right. MARRY you. AN' T BE WORSE Be you CAN' T THAN MY JOB. § A BORING & ILL- PAID JOB

canvas_summaries.ocr_text: Men and women will respect each other more and care for each other more truly when they marry because they seek companionship and enter into real partnership. Where there is real equality of opportunity and of status, you will have real partnership. Partnership implies trust and confidence. Our homes should be founded, our industries built up, and our lives based on those qualities if we are ever to become free people in a free world. The children of today build the world of tomorrow. ideas and impressions made on children' s minds form and colour all their adult lives. God has implanted His Spirit in mankind, not in man alone. Men and women are equally essential to the progress of civilisation and the continuance of the race. Boys and girls should be taught while young to shoulder responsibility and realize their potentialities. They should have a love of justice and freedom implanted in them in childhood, and be encouraged in a sense of real comradeship. This they are unlikely to achieve in any real measure if one sex is taught that it is superior to the other. While men are paid more money than women for identical work, women' s status must suffer. The status of all that is considered " Women' s Sphere " automatic ally suffers also, including the home, children, and all the arts of home- making.

canvas_summaries.ocr_text: EQUAL PAY FOR EQUAL WORK Is in the best interests of Men and Women Because, working as equals they will develop greater appreciation of each other' s needs, both at work and in the home. This understanding between the sexes is a first essential if we hope later to achieve understand ing between the nations. Married men have responsibilities which bachelors and some women do not have. In order to help them to meet these responsibilities they have tax rebate and are to have family allowances. That is just and proper. To pay them all higher wages than women who are doing identical work is unjust and wrong. Many women have to support dependents, and some men have no such liabilities. It is not generally the practice to pay men according to their responsibilities. The rate of pay should be fixed according to the work done. That is fair to all. The opulent Bachelor and the over- burdened Married Man receive the same Pay for the same Work-- Why differentiate against Women?

30 Please return to h. w. w. IT 4), bermmell food. EQUAL WORK DESERVES EQUAL PAY! By MAVIS TATE M. P. ON BEHALF OF THE EQUAL PAY CAMPAIGN COMMITTEE
Equal Pay for Equal Work will Be in the NATIONAL Interest Benefit Industry Help to bring Peace to the World The Rate for the Job will Maintain fair wage standards Make certain that the right person does the job Equal Pay for Equal Work is Right and Just It is in the best interests of: The HOME MEN Married and Bachelors WOMEN Married and Spinsters CHILDREN and Young People EMPLOYEES and EMPLOYERS X olo IF YOU HAVE ANY DOUBTS READ ON!
EQUAL PAY- Why it will be in the National Interest IN proportion to its size and population our country has made a contribution to the waging of this war incomparably greater than that made by any other nation. In 1940 we stood alone to safeguard the world for freedom and democracy. We have an equally important contribution to make in the post- war world towards maintaining Peace and the freedom which has been so dearly bought. We must mobilise our best brains and characters now to deal with the problems ahead, and as a first step we must give the Rate for the Job. That will enable us to find the right people for the right positions, and we shall have real equality of opportunity. In this we are not ahead of other Nations WE LAG BEHIND! EQUAL PAY Russia, America and part of China are far ahead of us in granting equal pay. These countries have proved it to be beneficial and in the national interest. How much longer are we going to allow them to leap ahead in post- war Recon struction? [ WORK Wo Britain Tags behind
Why it will benefit Industry [ QUAL Pay is right and just, and where there is justice there is a spirit of contentment and comradeship among employees. If appointments are made on merit, irrespective of sex, the best brains and general ability receive recogni tion and work is done by those best able to do it. This means that the quality of our products will steadily improve and our export trade expand. Industry must benefit if people are doing the work for which they are best suited instead of that for which they have no special aptitude or liking simply because their labour is cheapest and most readily available. but bon SURE SACKED SHE' S CHEAPER.
EQUAL PAY FOR EQUAL WORK Why it will help to bring Peace to the World Because: NLY great wisdom and vision, allied to constructive imagination, can deal with the complex problems of the post- war world. These are the gifts of the few, and only given to some men and women. We need to make full use of all who are especially gifted. We just cannot afford to be limited to one sex when choosing our Leaders and Executives. Until we have Equal Pay for Equal Work the status of women workers will be lower than that of men and there will not be equality of opportunity for service. Om lan If we choose leaders mainly from the male sex there will be a terrible wastage of ability which is sorely needed to guide us to peace, prosperity and inter national understanding. Equal Pay for Equal Work is in the Best Interests of IS
THE RATE FOR THE JOB Why it will maintain Fair Wage Standards W HERE you have the Rate- for- the- job there will be no undercutting. In America, where Equal Pay in the Civil Service and the Teaching Profession is established, it has been proved to be of benefit. If you have women competing with men for the same job at lower pay, the women have little incentive to give of their best. They appreciate that they are neither engaged nor promoted on merit and may never compete on fair terms with men. Male labour also suffers if it is considered on no more convincing grounds than sex discrimination. On that basis, neither sex has proper opportunity for discover ing which work it can most ably perform. Square pegs in round holes always have and always will make the machinery squeak! America, Russia and China are not blind to these simple facts. WHAT MUST THEY THINK OF US? Are you for lagging or for leading? Because they will be engaged for their capacity and employed on work for which they are best suited. Because they will have a happy and contented staff.
EQUAL PAY FOR EQUAL WORK Why it is in the best interests of the Home The Rate- for- the- Job is in the best interests of the home for a very large number of reasons. Marriage, if it is rightly based and leads to the foundation of a true home and healthy, happy family life, is the supreme career for a woman. It should be regarded as a career and entered upon with full appreciation of its poten tialities, responsibilities and opportunities. O It should never be undertaken as the easiest means of obtaining leisure and security. Marriage entered upon in that spirit often ends in disillusioned parents, broken homes, and unhappy undisciplined children. Women should be able to earn security and apprecia tion of special ability as a right. MARRY you. AN' T BE WORSE Be you CAN' T THAN MY JOB. A BORING & ILL- PAID JOB
Men and women will respect each other more and care for each other more truly when they marry because they seek companionship and enter into real partnership. Where there is real equality of opportunity and of status, you will have real partnership. Partnership implies trust and confidence. Our homes should be founded, our industries built up, and our lives based on those qualities if we are ever to become free people in a free world. The children of today build the world of tomorrow. ideas and impressions made on children' s minds form and colour all their adult lives. God has implanted His Spirit in mankind, not in man alone. Men and women are equally essential to the progress of civilisation and the continuance of the race. Boys and girls should be taught while young to shoulder responsibility and realize their potentialities. They should have a love of justice and freedom implanted in them in childhood, and be encouraged in a sense of real comradeship. This they are unlikely to achieve in any real measure if one sex is taught that it is superior to the other. While men are paid more money than women for identical work, women' s status must suffer. The status of all that is considered " Women' s Sphere " automatic ally suffers also, including the home, children, and all the arts of home- making.
EQUAL PAY FOR EQUAL WORK Is in the best interests of Men and Women Because, working as equals they will develop greater appreciation of each other' s needs, both at work and in the home. This understanding between the sexes is a first essential if we hope later to achieve understand ing between the nations. Married men have responsibilities which bachelors and some women do not have. In order to help them to meet these responsibilities they have tax rebate and are to have family allowances. That is just and proper. To pay them all higher wages than women who are doing identical work is unjust and wrong. Many women have to support dependents, and some men have no such liabilities. It is not generally the practice to pay men according to their responsibilities. The rate of pay should be fixed according to the work done. That is fair to all. The opulent Bachelor and the over- burdened Married Man receive the same Pay for the same Work-- Why differentiate against Women?
U FOR EQUAL OF COURSE I EQUAL PAYS EQUAL WORK . TORY LIBERAL POLITICALLY IT IS ACCEPTED Because: WHY NOS! Each Political Party says it stands for Equal Pay for Equal Work! LABOUR The House of Commons voted in favour of Equal Pay in 1936 and again in 1944
